HEADWORD: Teleutospore
<hw>Te*leu"to*spore</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
completion + E. <ets>spore</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The
thick-celled winter or resting spore of the rusts (order
<ord>Uredinales</ord>), produced in late summer. See <xex>Illust.</xex>
of <er>Uredospore</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

